ENDF Incident-Proton Data                This page provides access to incident-proton evaluations first made available with Release 6 of ENDF/B-VI.  Most of these evaluations were generated using the GNASH nuclear model code at Los Alamos in connection with the APT project, and they extend to 150 MeV. For the light targets of interest for fusion studies, the evaluations were generated using the EDA R-matrix code at Los Alamos, and they are limited to lower energies.  The ``raw eval'' links give the original  ENDF-format evaluation, the ``browse eval'' links give a easy-to-read  HTML version of the evaluation, the ``view ps plot'' link connects to  a color Postscript file ready for viewing with ghostscript or printing  on a color printer at high resolution. IAEA Photonuclear Data                This page provides access to a set of photonuclear evaluations, processed data for the MCNP or MCNPX Monte Carlo codes, and plots of the photonuclear cross sections and distributions.  The  evaluations are a subset of the ones submitted to the IAEA  Coordinated Research Project (CRP) on photonuclear data; they are the ones that could be processed by NJOY and the ones that could be converted for processing.  The master source for these evaluations is      http://iaeand.iaea.or.at/photonuclear/ .     Evaluations were provided by the Los Alamos National Laboratory (LANL), the Korean Atomic Energy Institute (KAERI), the Japanese Atomic Energy Institute (JAERI), the Chinese Nuclear Data Center (CNDC), and a collaboration between IPPE/Obninsk and CDFE/Moscow (the BOFOD library). We were able to process the LANL, KAERI, and CNDC files as provided. A number of changes were needed for the BOFOD files, including a change  in the ENDF MT numbers used, inserting some missing fission nubar  information, and fixing one problem in the U-235 fission spectrum  representation.  We were not able to process or convert the JAERI  evaluations at this time.         ACE Files for MCNP and MCNPX Monte Carlo Codes           The individual evaluations were processed using the NJOY Nuclear Data Processing System, and the results have been combined into ``Type-1'' formatted ACE files, one for each contributing laboratory, and  a  corresponding set of XSDIR lines.  The ACE files can be copied into  your MCNP/MCNPX data area, and the XSDIR lines can be inserted into  your XSDIR file.    WARNING : These files are new and based on the first  generation of photonuclear evaluations.  They are provided for purposes  of  testing and validation , and they should be  treated with  caution  until more experience has been obtained.  We would  appreciate feedback from all of you ``friendly users'' to both Morgan White (morgan@lanl.gov) and Bob MacFarlane (ryxm@lanl.gov).
